REPORTER: Ma Yifan



The sudden outbreak of the office of the future delivery standards, operational management and the use of new technology to put forward higher requirements.





The sudden outbreak of the office of the future delivery standards, operational management and the use of new technology to put forward higher requirements.



With more than 15 million square meters of high end office space, more than one million white collar workers work in a high density environment -- as the white collar workers return to work after the festival -- Shanghai's office managers are under pressure.

Under the severe epidemic situation, in the face of the flow of people to work, most offices are as far as possible to do adequate epidemic prevention measures. Rerouting, taking your temperature Multiple Times a day, shutting down your air conditioning, increasing the amount of fresh air in your ventilation system, assigning employees to AB groups, and taking the elevator off peak are all routine responses.

Wen Xia, a white-collar worker working in a super-high-rise office building in Lujiazui, experienced a special working day.

She and her colleagues walked into their offices on the first day of work in Lujiazui's ultra-prime office block, where the temperature used to stay above 20c even when it snowed, the company advised its employees that as the air conditioning building was closing, everyone needed to be warm and warm.

In the past, weekday lunches were often served in restaurants near the office, in food courts or by takeout, and restaurants in the Lujiazui region were always hard to come by during the lunch rush, and this year's first meal after the festival was a packed lunch.

An organization has statistics, Shanghai high-end Office office workers will not bring their own rice, some people are no time, afraid of trouble, some people are unable to wipe away face.

"But now the vast majority of colleagues bring their own food, the company also arranged for everyone to use the microwave oven and the tea room, a small number of colleagues do not have the conditions to make their own lunch, brought their own hot pot to eat. The company has also prepared instant noodles, biscuits and other fast food for everyone. In short, we do not recommend eating out or ordering takeout.".

Another special case is, originally thought to wait for the elevator line, she found that the lobby is very few people, the elevator neither to wait, nor crowded. "Even better than usual, we used to have to wait in line for five or six minutes to get on the elevator during the morning rush hour, " he said.

Wen said he was also a special case in the company. First of all, not all teams need to be on the job. It is very necessary for the team to be on the job to send people to the office. Second, employees who return from other places to Shanghai before the 14-day isolation period can not return to the office, but the temperature flaw is Shanghai person, has not left Shanghai, therefore can become the company first batch arrives at post the staff.

The office building is the property of her company, which carefully dispenses face masks, hand sanitizers and other protective products to the first batch of employees on duty, as well as air disinfectants and preventive medicines.

In Shanghai Nanjing West Road Core Business District, Leed Platinum Grade Certified Office Building Societe Generale Taiguhui measures to do more closely. The project, jointly developed and managed by HKR International and swire properties, consists of two high rise office buildings, 250 meters high and 170 meters high, with a total floor area of 170,000 square meters.

On February 4,5 and 7 prior to the resumption of work, the Property Management Office of Swire Pacific issued successive circulars to all tenants on matters relating to the post-resumption control.

In the first notice, issued on February 4, socgen swire required all employees and visitors entering its office properties to wear face masks and check the estimated number of reworkers for each tenant, tenants are also urged to minimize the return of staff to the office.

At the same time, Societe Generale Taikoo Hui recommended to tenants "the first group and the second group" strategy, suggesting that tenants will be the same team of personnel into two groups, the first group since February 10 working in the Office for two weeks, the second team members telecommuted from home for two weeks, after which the first team and the second team swapped offices. Societe Generale Swire said that his company is also using this strategy.

In addition, Societe Generale will be different floors, each group has a different commute and lunch time, this can effectively reduce the elevator and lobby traffic, to avoid congestion and queuing.

For example, the low-rise 14th-16th floor is a group, the 11th-13th floor is b group, the 8th-10th floor is c group, these three groups in the morning to the office time is set at 8:00,8:30,9:00 respectively, the off-duty time is set at 17:00,17:30 and 18:00 respectively.

Societe Generale also recommends that no more than six people take the stairs at a time, and does not encourage tenant staff to use the stairs to shuttle between floors, even during the lunch rush.

The next day, Societe Generale issued another notice, adding that tenants must submit a 24-hour advance appointment list of visitors, all staff temperature above 37.3 C can not enter the office building.

On February 7, Societe Generale announced it would stop all air conditioning, including office areas, public walkways, elevator halls, toilets and all passenger and freight elevators, in an effort to reduce the possibility of any spread of the virus. Fresh air systems will also be turned on to help reduce bacteria and viruses through photocatalyst filters and electrostatic filters.

On February 10, the first day of the resumption of work, Societe Generale Taikoo Place showed a tight grip on every detail, including disinfecting the elevator buttons every 15 minutes, setting up multiple points in the building to provide disinfectant, and automating the robot to sterilize the floor, and take-out personnel shall not enter the office building, use instead of "no contact to take sideboard" and other measures.

Sun Hung Kai, a Hong kong-owned property developer, has a number of ultra-high-rise grade a office buildings in Shanghai, including Guojin Centre in Lujiazui, IAPM World Trade Square in Huaihai Road and ITC in Xuhui.

What if a high-rise office building with a high density of people found abnormal body temperature? In response to the resumption of work, Sun Hung Kai made a special set of emergency plans.

The Sun Hung Kai Properties told interface news that it has set up temperature measuring points at all entrances and exits of the group's office buildings in Shanghai, including shopping malls and office buildings, and even used non contact infrared thermometers in the office buildings, the machine has the temperature alarm function, once meets the body temperature abnormal person, will send out the beeper.

People with abnormal body temperature will then be taken to a temporary isolation room that has already been set up to wait for the arrival of CDC personnel, while the property staff will quickly disinfect their mobile lines and all contact facilities thoroughly.

All front-line employees of Sun Hung Kai's office properties are required to wear face masks and gloves and take temperature measurements before taking up their posts. In addition, the property is broadcast on a half-hour loop, remind everyone to wear a mask and take a temperature when entering public areas. All the concierge desks are equipped with disinfectant, which can be used by tenants and customers in need. In addition, close all public area air conditioning and increase the amount of fresh air and exhaust ventilation.

At a time when the development and control of the epidemic are not yet fully clear, the resumption of work poses a huge challenge to the operation of office buildings and commercial real estate, and a series of measures taken by the management of office buildings, in the future, it may also be a factor in tenants'choice of properties.

Jones Lang Lasalle pointed out that this emergency has set higher requirements for improving the delivery standards of health-related office buildings. Specifically, these include the addition of ultraviolet disinfection modules to the fresh air and return air systems, the addition of a non-contact body temperature monitoring system, the installation of an intelligent elevator system integrated gate system, and the installation of automatic periodic disinfection equipment in public areas.

Savills told interface news that a range of new technologies could become standard features in office buildings in the future.

After the outbreak, the intensity of epidemic control and technical measures will be strengthened, such as the use of human body heat sensor monitoring and cloud integration technology, real-time body temperature records, combined with face recognition technology, the system can quickly mark the abnormal body surface temperature, and the detection information can be synchronized to epidemic prevention or smart city management platform, so as to control and manage suspected patients in advance. The use of office transport robots can optimize elevator efficiency and reduce the risk of infection.

The Traditional Security and fire protection work mostly depends on the professional degree and the degree of engagement of the practitioners, and under the background of the current high human cost and the epidemic environment, aIOT (artificial intelligence AI + IoT sensor IoT) can greatly reduce the quota of traditional personnel, reduce the cost of manpower at the same time can achieve Factor of safety, security efficiency.

In addition to affected by the epidemic, office operations increased pressure, in the aftermath of the epidemic, it can be expected that the office market will continue to be under pressure at the rental end.

Jones Lang Lasalle believes the outbreak will have a greater negative impact on the a-grade office market in mainland China and Hong Kong.

On the one hand, lease activity will significantly cool down in the short term before the epidemic is fully under control. Due to the delay of rework, health and safety concerns, on-site inspection, lease agreement signing, decoration and other activities will be subject to greater restrictions in the short term, real estate decision-making will be delayed, new rental demand in the short term or will be very limited.

On the other hand, the uncertainty of the market and economic environment will significantly affect the short-term confidence in the market, enterprises will adopt more cautious leasing strategy.

From the sub-sectors, Jones Lang Lasalle believes that the short-term impact of the outbreak on import and export trade, retail, tourism and offline education and training industries will be the most significant negative impact. After the outbreak ends, new opportunities are brewing in the health and insurance industry, TMT, an online service provider, and environmental industries.

During the SARS epidemic in 2003, office rents fell for about two or three quarters, before quickly returning to an upward trajectory, while Hong Kong experienced a sharp rise in office rents after the SARS epidemic. But Jones Lang Lasalle said that was not expected to happen again.

Back then, Beishangguang was in a period of rapid economic growth, while these cities were already in a period of falling rents due to excessive new supply growth, and Hong Kong office rents have just started to fall from record highs, so the negative impact of this outbreak on office building demand has been apparent.

However, compared with the large-scale rent reduction in commercial real estate, office rent reduction is not active.

Some of the interviewed office owners told the interface news reporter that as the epidemic is not yet clear, whether or not to implement rent concessions is not yet known, can not respond.

Jones Lang Lasalle pointed out that the negative impact was mainly concentrated in the short-term market. In the medium to long-term overall market, the fundamentals remained sound. With the follow-up of relevant supporting policies, further deepening of technological development and financial openness, the office building market will still have medium-and long-term good, short-term backlog of market demand is expected to end after the outbreak of accelerated release.
